The hardest part of my job, and the most frustrating, is also the most exciting: to never do anything without AI. 

I never modify an Excel or a PowerPoint manually without using the AI agent. I never send an email without having the agent write and send the email. 

Since this week, I'm trying to get even more AI-pilled and not answer any Teams message myself… only my agent does. 

It’s fascinating to see the potential, and yet it’s super frustrating because it doesn’t quite work. So many times I want to type the email myself or modify the Word doc…

BUT suffering from these imperfections pushes me to fix everything so my agent can handle my day-to-day tasks from start to finish.

